Pre-Game Insights: Czech Republic needed at least one point to stay in contention for a place in Euro 2024's knockout phase.
Head coach Ivan Hasek considered freshening up the front line in pursuit of victory.
Patrik Schick, who scored five times at Euro 2020, was not likely to be dropped.
Jan Kuchta could make way for Adam Hlozek or Mojmir Chytil.
Pavel Sulc, who finished second in the Czech league's goalscoring charts, was a surprise starter and his place was in jeopardy.
Fiorentina playmaker Antonin Barak could offer a creative presence in midfield.
Captain Tomas Soucek and Vladimir Coufal, both from West Ham United, were in the starting XI.
Goalkeeper Jindrich Stanek started ahead of Matej Kovar.
